###### Proposition 4.12.

The type E\_{7} strong exchange equations 7 are affinely invariant.

* Proof.

  Since the equations f^{E\_{7}}\_{A,B} are the exact equations 4 on cross polytopes, the corresponding statement follows from Proposition 4.4. Consider f^{E\_{7}}, and \mu\in\mathbb{T}^{V(3\_{21})}. For \varphi:\mathbb{R}^{8}\to\mathbb{R} affine linear, we have that x\_{A}\odot x\_{-A} evaluated at \mu+\varphi|\_{V(3\_{21})} yields \mu\_{A}+\mu\_{-A}+2\varphi(0). Therefore, \mu attains the minimum at least twice if and only if \mu+\varphi does.
