Over the Krasner hyperfield, the strong exchange equations (7) are equivalent to the symmetric exchange axiom of Borovik, Gelfand, and White [4], which they conjectured to be equivalent to the Coxeter matroid axioms (e.g. the maximality property) in all minuscule types [3, Section 6.16]. By means of an exhaustive search, we prove that this conjecture holds in E\_{7}.

###### Theorem 4.13.

All Coxeter matroids of type (E\_{7},P\_{7}) satisfy the strong exchange condition.

In combination with known results in the other types we conclude that in all types except B\_{n}, all minuscule Coxeter matroids satisfy the strong exchange axiom. Moreover, Theorem 4.13 implies that the relations on the proper faces of 3\_{21} are already sufficient to guarantee a subdivision consists of strong Coxeter matroid polytopes.

###### Theorem 4.14.

A height function \mu induces a strong matroidal subdivision of 3\_{21} if and only if it is contained in \bigcap\_{(A,B)}V^{\text{Trop}}(f^{E\_{7}}\_{A,B}), where (A,B) runs over all pairs of elements of W(E\_{7})/P\_{7} with d(A,B)=2.

However, it is still open whether all \mu satisfying the equivalent conditions of Theorem 4.14 are in the Dressian.

###### Conjecture 1.

The support of \operatorname{Dr}(E\_{7},P\_{7}) is equal to the support of \bigcap V^{\text{Trop}}(f^{E\_{7}}\_{A,B}).

